        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üö® CHAPTER TWO: The Investigation</div>
            <p>After 30 tractors went missing in three months, farmers called the police. Detectives traced the parts being sold online back to Brer Sheep's "salvage yard."</p>
            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Detective</span>: "These serial numbers match stolen tractors."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "Must be a coincidence!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Detective</span>: "All 30 of them?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "...big coincidence?"
            </div>
            <p>They found stolen tractors, stolen parts, and a whiteboard where Brer Sheep had literally written "TONIGHT'S TRACTOR TARGET: Farmer Brown's new Kubota."</p>
            <p>The evidence was overwhelming. And dumb.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">‚öñÔ∏è CHAPTER THREE: The Charges</div>
            <p>Brer Sheep was charged with 30 counts of grand theft auto (agricultural edition), operating a chop shop, and "criminal stupidity" (not a real charge, but it should be).</p>
            <p>He got 5 years probation, had to pay restitution for all the tractors, and was banned from owning anything with an engine for 10 years.</p>
            <div class="dialogue">
                <span class="character">Judge</span>: "Do you understand that stealing tractors is a FELONY?"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "I understand that NOW, Your Honor."<br><br>
                <span class="character">Judge</span>: "You wrote your targets on a WHITEBOARD!"<br><br>
                <span class="character">Brer Sheep</span>: "...I like to stay organized?"
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chapter" data-narrate="true">
            <div class="chapter-title">üìö EPILOGUE</div>
            <p>Brer Sheep closed the chop shop, sold his remaining inventory (legally this time), and got a job at an actual legitimate salvage yard where everything was properly documented.</p>
            <p>He learned that "no questions asked" pricing is usually a red flag, and that whiteboards are admissible in court.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="moral">
            <p><strong>üöó THE MORAL üöó</strong></p>
            <p>Chop shops are illegal. Obvious chop shops get caught immediately.</p>
            <p><em>Also: Don't write your crimes on a whiteboard.<br>
            And "I found it" is not a valid chain of custody.<br>
            And maybe just buy parts from legitimate dealers.</em></p>
